# Caboodle Conventions

## Project overview

Caboodle is a monorepo with two packages: a Next.js 16 site (`packages/caboodle-site`) and a Lit Web Component library (`packages/object-components`). Object data lives in `data/objects/*.json` (26 files) with a shared TypeScript schema in `data/schema.ts`. Each object can define **`objectViews`**: an array of `ObjectView` entries, each with a **view context** (`context`), `viewType` `'list'` or `'detail'`, and (for list views) optional `shapes` for `list`, `grid`, and `table` (`ShapeSpec`). The WC library is currently rebuilding ‚Äî only `ren-student-row.ts` and `shared/tokens.ts` remain on disk.

## File organization

- **Site pages**: `packages/caboodle-site/app/{route}/page.tsx` (Next.js App Router)
- **React components**: `packages/caboodle-site/components/{category}/ComponentName.tsx`
- **Lit Web Components**: `packages/object-components/src/ren-{object}-{component}.ts` (rebuilding) ‚Äî components implement presentations aligned to **object views** (e.g. a list-shape row); naming may still use legacy suffixes like `-row` until the library is fully rebuilt
- **Styles**: `packages/caboodle-site/styles/` ‚Äî tokens.css, layouts.css, globals.css, components.css
- **Object data**: `data/objects/{slug}.json` ‚Äî one file per object (26 files)
- **Data schema**: `data/schema.ts` ‚Äî TypeScript types shared by site and WC library
- **Data loading**: `packages/caboodle-site/lib/objects.ts` and `lib/systems.ts`
- **Server actions**: `packages/caboodle-site/app/actions.ts` ‚Äî updateAttribute, updateCTA
- **Preview registry**: `packages/caboodle-site/lib/preview-registry.ts` ‚Äî maps **view contexts** (from `objectViews`) to preview components
- **Static assets**: `packages/caboodle-site/public/` ‚Äî logo, icons, framework logos, PWA icons
- **Reference docs**: `docs/requirements/` (see `docs/requirements/STATUS.md` for status)
- **Architecture decisions**: `docs/decisions/`

## Routing

The site uses system-based routing for the Object Library:

- `/` ‚Äî Home
- `/objects` ‚Äî Object Library (system catalog)
- `/objects/[systemSlug]` ‚Äî System Detail (object grid)
- `/objects/[systemSlug]/[objectSlug]` ‚Äî Object Guide (tabbed detail)
- `/objects/[systemSlug]/[objectSlug]/views/[viewSlug]` ‚Äî View Inspector
- `/design-system` ‚Äî Component style guide (not in nav)
- `/glossary`, `/process`, `/resources` ‚Äî Placeholder pages

Systems are derived from each object's `identity.products` field via `lib/systems.ts`.

## Component conventions

- **React components** handle site-specific UI: navigation, tabs, data tables, config panels, preview renderers, roster components
- **Lit Web Components** handle object representations for list/detail **object views** and list/grid/table shapes (cards, rows, profiles, headers ‚Äî currently rebuilding)
- Client components use `'use client'` directive; server components are the default
- Tabs component has full ARIA support (tablist, tab, tabpanel, keyboard navigation)
- Server/client split: page.tsx loads data, client component receives props for interactivity

## CSS conventions

- Entry point is `styles/globals.css` which imports: tokens ‚Üí layouts
- Component styles in `styles/components.css`
- Add new tokens to `tokens.css` ‚Äî use token categories: `--color-*`, `--font-*`, `--s-*`, `--radius-*`, `--shadow-*`
- Never modify `layouts.css` ‚Äî compose existing Every Layout primitives instead
- Use modular scale tokens (`--s-5` to `--s5`) for all spacing
- Use logical properties (`margin-block-start`, `padding-inline`) instead of physical
- Web Components consume CSS custom properties through shadow DOM for theming (`--ren-*` tokens)

## TypeScript conventions

- Strict mode enabled in both packages
- Object data types defined in `data/schema.ts` ‚Äî import from there
- Use `ObjectDefinition` as the top-level type for object data
- Use `SystemDefinition` for system groupings
- Data loading via `lib/objects.ts` ‚Äî `getObjectBySlug()`, `getAllObjects()`, `getAllObjectSlugs()`
- System loading via `lib/systems.ts` ‚Äî `getAllSystems()`, `getSystemBySlug()`, `getAllSystemSlugs()`

## Object identity system

- **Core objects** use `object_icon.svg`
- **Object variations** use `object-variation_icon.svg`
- **Domain objects** use `domain-object_icon.svg`
- No per-object colors or avatar shapes ‚Äî icon type is the visual differentiator
- `ObjectIcon` component resolves the correct icon based on `objectType`

## Accessibility

- WCAG 2.1 AA target
- All images must have `alt` text (decorative images use `alt=""` with `aria-hidden="true"`)
- Focus styles via `:focus-visible` (defined in globals.css)
- Keyboard-navigable tab interfaces with arrow key support
- Material Icons must include `aria-hidden="true"` when decorative
- ARIA roles on all interactive components (tablist/tab/tabpanel, radio groups)

## Navigation

Navigation is handled by the `MainNav` React component, which uses `usePathname()` to set `aria-current="page"` automatically. Routes: `/`, `/objects`, `/resources`, `/process`, `/glossary`. The `/design-system` route exists but is not linked in the nav.

## Asset paths

All assets are in `packages/caboodle-site/public/`:
- Logo: `/img/caboodle-logo.svg`
- Object icons: `/img/object_icon.svg`, `/img/domain-object_icon.svg`, `/img/object-variation_icon.svg`
- Framework logos: `/img/react.svg`, `/img/angular.svg`, `/img/vuedotjs.svg`, `/img/webcomponentsdotorg.svg`

## Commands

- `npm run dev` ‚Äî start Next.js dev server
- `npm run build` ‚Äî build WC library + site
- `npm run build:components` ‚Äî build WC library only
- `npm run build:site` ‚Äî build site only
